ED_Title: Election of the Vice-Presidents of the General Assembly at its seventy-sixth session
ED_DecisionText: At its 72nd plenary meeting, on 7 June 2021, the General Assembly, in accordance with rule 30 of the rules of procedure of the Assembly and paragraphs 2 and 3 of the annex to resolution 33/138 of 19 December 1978, elected the following 21 Member States as Vice-Presidents of the General Assembly at its seventy-sixth session: BANGLADESH, BELGIUM, CHINA, COSTA RICA, CÔTE D’IVOIRE, DOMINICAN REPUBLIC, EGYPT, EQUATORIAL GUINEA, FINLAND, FRANCE, HAITI, KUWAIT, LAO PEOPLE’S DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC, MOZAMBIQUE, PHILIPPINES, RUSSIAN FEDERATION, SIERRA LEONE, SLOVENIA, UNITED KINGDOM OF GREAT BRITAIN AND NORTHERN IRELAND, UNITED REPUBLIC OF TANZANIA AND UNITED STATES OF AMERICA.
ED_Disclaimer: The final text of this decision will be contained in document A/75/49 (Vol. III) after editorial review.
